# ROAM Codebase Rules

## Stack
- React Native + Expo Router (file-based routing in app/)
- Supabase (auth, Postgres, edge functions, Realtime)
- Zustand (state management in lib/store.ts)
- RevenueCat (subscriptions)
- TypeScript strict mode

## Design System (lib/constants.ts)
- Colors: bg=#080F0A, sage=#7CAF8A, cream=#F5EDD8, coral=#E8614A, accentGold=#C9A84C
- Fonts: Cormorant Garamond Bold (headers), DM Sans (body), DM Mono (labels)
- Dark-only UI. No light mode.
- NO EMOJIS ANYWHERE. Use colored dots, text pills, or lucide-react-native icons.

## Architecture
- All AI calls go through `supabase/functions/claude-proxy/` — NEVER call Anthropic directly from client
- Free tier: 1 trip/month, enforced server-side in edge function
- Pro tier: unlimited, managed via RevenueCat
- Guest mode: anonymous auth + waitlist email capture

## Code Standards
- Immutability always — never mutate, return new objects
- Files: 200-400 lines typical, 800 max
- Functions: <50 lines
- Nesting: <4 levels deep
- Handle errors explicitly at every level
- Validate all inputs at system boundaries
- No hardcoded secrets — use env vars

## Key Files
- `lib/claude.ts` — System prompt, callClaude(), buildTripPrompt()
- `lib/store.ts` — Zustand store (session, trips, isPro, currency)
- `lib/constants.ts` — COLORS, FONTS, SPACING, RADIUS
- `lib/types/itinerary.ts` — Itinerary type + parseItinerary() validator
- `lib/pro-gate.ts` — Feature gating (free vs pro)
- `lib/revenue-cat.ts` — RevenueCat init, purchase, restore

## Conventions
- Conventional commits: type(scope): description
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
- All Supabase tables use RLS with auth.uid() ownership checks
- Edge functions use Deno.env.get() for secrets
- Web builds stub expo-haptics and react-native-view-shot (see lib/haptics.ts, lib/view-shot.ts)

## Testing
- TSC check: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Web build: `npx expo export --platform web`
- Always verify new code compiles before committing

## Do NOT
- Use emojis in UI code
- Put API keys in EXPO_PUBLIC_ vars (except Supabase anon key, Google Places)
- Call Anthropic API directly from client code
- Use `WITH CHECK (true)` in RLS policies
- Ship console.log with sensitive data
- Mutate state — always create new objects
